<div id="about-the-community" class="section-spacer">
    <h2 class="sect-title">About Abbeydale</h2>
    <div class="col-grid-2">
        <div>
            <p class="par-lg">A vibrant residential neighborhood located in the North-East quadrant, Abbeydale is bordered by 68 Street E on the west, the Canadian National Railway on the south, East Freeway on the east and the Trans-Canada Highway on the north.</p>
            <p class="par-xl">The community association in Abbeydale is highly active and focuses on recreational programs for the youth and families residing within the community.</p>
            <p class="par-lg">Regardless of whether you are a young couple, a family with kids or an elderly planning to settle in a relaxing neighborhood post-retirement, the community in Abbeydale offers a myriad of housing options at irresistible prices.</p>
            <p class="par-lg">A majority of the homes for sale in Abbeydale comprise single-family detached units and townhomes with a few recently developed apartment condominiums. Detached units are commonly listed at an average price of $390,000.</p>
        </div>
